summary: I was babysitting for the first time (3 boys) and the oldest one (he’s 7) said he watches Andi Mack. He then started freaking...
body: I was babysitting for the first time (3 boys) and the oldest one (he’s 7) said he watches Andi Mack. He then started freaking out over Jonah after I showed him Asher’s Chemistry vid and later said “I’m like Cyrus! I like Jonah too!” It was honestly so cute and pure. His cousin (6) who also watches didn’t find anything weird about it and thought it was normal. I asked if had a crush on Jonah (before he had said he was like Cyrus) and he said “noooooo” and then his cousin said “Yes he does” and then the 7 year old looked at him and said “You promised you wouldn’t tell!” and then they both started laughing. THIS IS PROOF THAT REPRESENTATION IN KIDS SHOWS MATTER!

summary: If TJ makes any episode appearances (which we all know he will), do you think they'll be Cyrus-centered episodes? Usually they...
question: If TJ makes any episode appearances (which we all know he will), do you think they'll be Cyrus-centered episodes? Usually they stick in 2 different plots (sometimes 3) into one episode, so do you think they'd be focusing more on the storyline we all deserve?
answer: The thing with Andi Mack is well, Andi is the main character, So calling them Cyrus-centered episodes is a stretch (Even Cyrus Bash Mitzvah episode was more focused on Jandi drama) but we are definitely getting some good Tyrus scenes coming our way, but the Jandi drama will be the main focus in the coming episodes. Maybe the funeral episode could be the only Cyrus-centric of the whole season.

summary:
Guys, remember how the episode was called "Wedding Dream"?
This could be a dream sequence. They had done special effects so it...
body:
Guys, remember how the episode was called “Wedding Dream”?

This could be a dream sequence. They had done special effects so it could be that Bowie says yes and then either one of them start having nightmares that lead to second thoughts about their wedding. I don’t think that they’d get engaged and then a few weeks later get married-they don’t have the time or money for that.

Or they could do a major time skip, which I’d enjoy cuz we’d finally know when in time we are. But I feel like that’d be unlikely because of the cliff hangers from the finale
